Amal Hussein is an engineer, community organizer, and budding entrepreneur. She identifies as an expert problem solver and enjoys navigating through the many challenges of building resilient and accessible production applications. She is starting a new role as Principal Software Engineer at a top-secret-yet-to-be-announced-company, where she will be focused on building solutions to annually save the planet millions of gallons of fuel.

Previously, Amal was an Engineering Manager at npm Inc and where she led a team focused on maintaining and extending internal microservices for the npm Registry. Before that, as a Sr Open Web Engineer & Technical Lead at Bocoup, she worked on a variety of impactful projects that helped push the web platform forward by making it more predictable, interoperable, and inclusive.

Amal lives in Boston, Massachusetts with her fiancee. They enjoying traveling, eating good food, and traveling to eat good food.

name: Mock Practical Frontend Interview
description:
Ideally, we'll have one person volunteer to be the interviewee, but if no one volunteers, we could mob program the challenge. Comment below if you'd like to volunteer to be the interviewee. We'll probably spend around 45 minutes on a coding challenge and then have a group discussion afterwards. The interview will be recorded. If you'd like to remain anonymous, you can turn your camera off and use an alias name. Challenge will be done using Code Sandbox https://codesandbox.io/.

Here's an example of what the experience will be like: https://youtu.be/kfA0WMWeEDs

name: Intro to Three.js
description:
Presenter will be Yoel Morad https://www.linkedin.com/in/yoelmorad/.

Yoel will give a general introduction to Three.js. He'll go over why creating immersive experiences for users are important and how to set up the basic constructs of a three project. https://threejs.org/
